  "stem": "<figure class=\"table\"><table border=\"1\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th style=\"width: 47.1721%; text-align: center;\" scope=\"col\">Area (square feet)</th>\n<th style=\"width: 47.3335%; text-align: center;\" scope=\"col\">Water (gallons)</th>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 47.1721%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"2,520\"><mn>2,520</mn>\n</math></td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.3335%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"4,536\"><mn>4,536</mn>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 47.1721%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"3,780\"><mn>3,780</mn>\n</math></td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.3335%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"6,804\"><mn>6,804</mn>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width: 47.1721%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"5,040\"><mn>5,040</mn>\n</math></td>\n<td style=\"width: 47.3335%; text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"9,072\"><mn>9,072</mn>\n</math></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></figure>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">The buildings of a shopping center are designed to allow water to drain from the roof into gutters on the sides of the buildings. The table shows the relationship between the area <math alttext=\"x\"><mi>x</mi>\n</math>, in square feet, of a roof and the amount of water <math alttext=\"f left parenthesis x right parenthesis\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>, in gallons, drained from the roof into the gutters over a certain period of time. Which equation could define <math alttext=\"f\"><mi>f</mi>\n</math>?</p>",
